1️⃣ Spring Core

What it is:
Spring Core provides the foundation of the Spring framework. It handles object creation, lifecycle, and configuration.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Key Concepts:

Beans & BeanFactory / ApplicationContext

Bean = Object managed by Spring container

BeanFactory – basic container

ApplicationContext – advanced container (events, internationalization)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Bean Scope

Singleton, Prototype, Request, Session, GlobalSession


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Bean Lifecycle

Initialization, destruction, @PostConstruct, @PreDestroy

Configuration

XML-based (legacy)

Annotation-based (@Component, @Configuration, @Bean)

Java-based config (modern, recommended)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2️⃣ Dependency Injection (DI)

What it is:
DI is the core concept of Spring: Spring injects dependencies instead of creating them manually. This makes your code loosely coupled.

Types of DI:

1.Constructor Injection

2.Setter Injection

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Annotations:

@Autowired → inject dependency

@Qualifier → choose which bean to inject

@Component → class managed by Spring

@Service / @Repository / @Controller → specialized components
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
